## Complete Test Matrix Required

### CATEGORY 1: CONTRACT TESTS
These verify contracts/invariants - what MUST remain true.

#### 1.1 Configuration Contracts
- Valid YAML loading from file and dict
- Invalid strategy rejection (ID generation strategies)
- Missing required fields validation
- Duplicate analyzer names detection
- Configuration default values
- Type coercion (strings to numbers, booleans)
- Nested configuration validation
- Environment variable override mechanisms
- Schema completeness validation

#### 1.2 ID Generation Contracts
- Deterministic generation: same content → same ID
- Different content → different IDs
- ID format validation (SHA256-16 must be 16 chars hex, SHA256-32 must be 32 chars, UUID4 format)
- Prefix/suffix preservation
- Hash strategy correctness
- Custom strategy registration
- Invalid strategy rejection
- Empty content handling
- Large content handling (>100MB)

#### 1.3 Metadata Sidecar Contracts
- Exact match discovery (basename.json)
- Wildcard discovery (*.json in directory)
- Parent directory search
- Malformed JSON graceful failure
- Missing metadata returns None (not invented data)
- Metadata precedence when multiple strategies match
- Encoding fallback for metadata files
- Empty metadata file handling

#### 1.4 Output Structure Contracts
- manifest.json exists at root
- Each document has its own directory
- No loose documents in output root (only manifest.json and .keepme)
- Directory naming uses document ID
- File naming conventions (doc_id.ext, extracted.txt, rd_*.json, sc_*.json)
- Manifest JSON schema validation
- Success rate calculation accuracy
- Duplicate tracking in manifest
- Error summary completeness

#### 1.5 Safety Invariants
- raw_bytes never modified during processing
- Metadata never invented (only found or None)
- HTML loading does not execute scripts
- PDF loading preserves content
- No data leakage between documents
- Concurrent processing safety (if enabled)
- File permissions preservation
- Encoding preservation (input → output bytes identical hash)

#### 1.6 Document Loader Contracts
- Text extraction matches format:
  - PDF: text + images → extracted text
  - HTML: visible text only, scripts/styles removed
  - TXT: raw text with encoding fallback
  - JSON: pretty-printed or raw per config
  - XML: flattened structure
  - DOCX: text preserved
  - DOC: conversion or rejection if unavailable
- max_text_length enforced (truncation or error)
- Encoding detection and fallback
- Binary format rejection for text extractors
- Empty document handling

#### 1.7 Scanner Contracts
- Filesystem discovery with depth limits
- ZIP extraction with configurable max depth
- Supported format filtering
- Directory traversal security (no ../ escaping)
- Duplicate file detection
- Symlink handling (follow/skip)
- Permission error handling
- Pattern matching (glob patterns if supported)

#### 1.8 Analyzer Pipeline Contracts
- HTML analyzer removes scripts when configured
- XML analyzer flattens to text
- JSON analyzer pretty-prints valid JSON
- Analyzer chain execution order
- Disabled analyzers skipped
- Error in one analyzer doesn't fail pipeline
- Analyzer results captured in manifest

