### STEP 3: Bug Fix - ZIP Premature Temp-Dir Cleanup

Root cause: ctx.cleanup() was placed in the finally block of each document processing iteration
inside IngestService.ingest(). For a ZIP archive containing multiple files, the shared temp
directory was deleted after processing the first document, making all subsequent files from
the same archive unreadable at load time.

Fix applied to core/ingestion/ingest_service.py:
- Added scan_context = None before the scan loop
- Assigned scan_context = ctx on each iteration (keeps a reference across documents)
- Removed ctx.cleanup() from the per-document finally block
- Added outer finally section that calls scan_context.cleanup() once after the full scan

Test strengthened in test/e2e/t_zip_resilience_e2e.py:
- test_ingest_nested_zip_extracts_inner_and_outer_documents:
  Added root.txt as a sibling entry inside outer.zip alongside inner.zip.
  Assertion updated from len(manifest.ingested) == 1 to == 2.
  Verifies both outer/inner/inner.txt and outer/root.txt appear in the manifest.

Final result: 86 passed, 1 skipped (Windows symlink without privileges)